  "text": "A good deal of effort has gone toward the development of novel delivery systems to improve therapeutic efficacy and reduce adverse reactions. To this end, nanotechnology has been applied to delivery systems, which, in general, enhances efficacy and potency by increasing surface area, solubility, and dissolution rate, and through the rapid onset of therapeutic action. Indeed, several drug delivery systems have been applied for docetaxel thus far, including docetaxel-loaded nanoparticles (5), self-emulsified docetaxel [CITATION_1] , malic acid-esterified docetaxel [CITATION_2] , and PEGylated liposomes [CITATION_3] and N-palmitoyl chitosan-anchored liposome (9) for docetaxel.",
